        "commit_message_instructions": "Generate commit messages in the following strict format:\n\n## Title format\n[Type]() module: short imperative description (max 10 words)\n\nType must be one of: Fix, Feature, Docs, Test, Refactor, Workaround — choose the one that best matches the primary intent. The first letter of the Type MUST be capitalized.\n\nModule: infer from the top-level directory of changed files (e.g., runtime, kmd, compiler, device_libs, lepton, lib).\n\n## Body format\nRoot Cause:\n<Describe the root cause clearly, within 60 words>\nSolution:\n1. As title\nTest:\nCI\nImpact area:\n<module name>\nFix status:\nDone\n\n## Rules\n- Leave the JIRA ID empty in the title like `[Type]()`.\n- Use imperative mood, first letter capitalized in the title description.\n- Keep the title concise: no more than 10 words (excluding [Type]() module: prefix).\n- Do NOT add any blank lines between Root Cause, Solution, Test, Impact area, and Fix status sections."
    },
